/* Motion preference: only animate if user allows */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
  body, article {
    transition: background 1.8s ease, color 1s ease, line-height 1.8s ease;
  }
}

/* Font scaling: use relative units */
html {
  font-size: 100%; /* respects user’s default */
}
body {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
}
h1, h2, h3 { line-height: 1.2; margin: 1.6em 0 0.8em; }

/* Ensure all spacing expands proportionally */
article { padding: 6vh 8vw; max-width: 42rem; }

/* Print fallback */
@media print {
  body {
    background: #fff !important;
    color: #000 !important;
  }
  article {
    break-inside: avoid;
    page-break-inside: avoid;
    padding: 0 0 1.5em;
    box-shadow: none;
  }
  hr.separator {
    border-top: 1px solid #ccc;
    opacity: 1;
  }
}
```

**How these additions behave**

* `prefers-reduced-motion` — all backgrounds and fades stay static for readers who need still pages.  
* Relative units (`rem`, `em`) ensure that any change in the browser’s base text size keeps rhythm and spacing consistent.  
* The print media rule resets background colors and shadows and prevents awkward page splits, so a printed copy remains calm, legible, and uncluttered.

With these tweaks, the design maintains the same soft tempo across phones, tablets, desktop, and paper—quiet technology serving the same emotional rhythm.

